---
name: agent-mcp-toolsource
version: 0.1.0
description: Use a downstream MCP server's tools as agent tools via mcpToolSource (jvm/js backends).
---

# MCP tools as agent tools

`mcpToolSource` turns every tool a connected MCP server exposes into an `AgentTool`, so the
agent loop can call external MCP tools alongside the app's own — the consumer half of the
bridge. Requires a jvm/js backend (the MCP client is unavailable on the interpreter).

[mcpConnect](std/mcp/client.ssc)
[Transport](std/mcp/server.ssc)
[mcpToolSource](std/agent-mcp.ssc)

```scalascript
val client = mcpConnect(Transport.Spawn("node", List("examples/mcp-server-tools.js")))
val tools = mcpToolSource(client)
println("imported " + tools.length.toString + " MCP tools as agent tools:")
tools.foreach { t => println("  " + t.name + " — " + t.description) }
// `tools` can now be passed to runAgent(...) alongside the app's own AgentTools.
client.close()
```
